nested_items.description: Object that describes a spectral Config.

nested_items.name: bandwidth
nested_items.description: Bandwidth of a spectral Config. AWS Ground Station currently has the following bandwidth limitations:
For AntennaDownlinkDemodDecodeconfig, valid values are between 125 kHz to 650 MHz.
For AntennaDownlinkconfig valid values are between 10 kHz to 54 MHz.
For AntennaUplinkConfig, valid values are between 10 kHz to 54 MHz.

nested_items.name: centerFrequency
nested_items.description: Center frequency of a spectral Config. Valid values are between 2200 to 2300 MHz and 7750 to 8400 MHz for downlink and 2025 to 2120 MHz for uplink.

nested_items.name: units
nested_items.description: Frequency units.

nested_items.name: value
nested_items.description: Frequency value. Valid values are between 2200 to 2300 MHz and 7750 to 8400 MHz for downlink and 2025 to 2120 MHz for uplink.

nested_items.name: polarization
nested_items.description: Polarization of a spectral Config. Capturing both "RIGHT_HAND" and "LEFT_HAND" polarization requires two separate configs.
